<subSubSection pageId="170" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="170.[151,1437,1556,1797]" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,506,1700,1725]" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[517,666,1700,1725]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="New Ireland" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">New Ireland</collectingRegion>
: 1, 2, 5.—General distribution: Red Sea, East Africa, 
<collectingCountry box="[1309,1432,1700,1725]" name="Seychelles" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,286,1735,1760]" name="Madagascar" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and Mascarenes east to 
<collectingCountry box="[567,629,1735,1760]" name="Palau" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Palau</collectingCountry>
and New 
<collectingCountry box="[748,832,1735,1760]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Guinea</collectingCountry>
, north to southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1048,1115,1737,1760]" name="Japan" pageId="170" pageNumber="171">Japan</collectingCountry>
, south to Western Australia. Solitary or in groups, on coastal reefs, in lagoons and on seaward reef slopes, 
<quantity box="[1023,1122,1772,1796]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="170" pageNumber="171" unit="m" value="45.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="10.0">10–80 m</quantity>
depth. Marine.
</paragraph>
